{"lemma":"ضَرْبُ","slug":"ضَرْبُ","root":"ض.ر.ب","root_slug":"ض-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضَرْب","root":"ضرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":55},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n25696","n25697","n25698","n25699"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike, to beat, to hit","examples":[{"text":"ضَرَبَ رَأْسَهُ بِٱلْجِدَارِ","english":"He hit his head against the wall."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shoot at, to fire at, to bombard","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to play"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to type (on a keyboard or typewriter)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to impose, to inflict","examples":[{"text":"ضُرِبَتْ عَلَيْهِمُ الذِّلَّةُ أَيْنَ مَا ثُقِفُوا إِلَّا بِحَبْلٍ مِنَ اللَّهِ وَحَبْلٍ مِنَ النَّاسِ","english":"Ignominy shall be their portion wheresoever they are found save (where they grasp) a rope from Allah and a rope from men."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leave, to abandon, to turn away from, to forsake"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sting (of a scorpion)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pitch (a tent)","examples":[{"text":"ضَرَبَ خَيْمَةً","english":"to pitch a tent"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to coin, to mint, to strike"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to seal, to stamp"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to erase"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cast, to throw, to set, to put","examples":[{"text":"ضَرَبَ الفَخًّا عَلَى الطَائِرِ","english":"he threw the snare over the bird"},{"text":"ضَرَبَ بَيْنَهُمَا سَدًْا","english":"he set a barrier between (the two of) them"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be long (of the night)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set or posit as an example or make a simile of, to be proverbial with","examples":[{"text":"خِلَاط\nبكَسر أوله، وآخره طاء مهملة: بلدة عامرة مشهورة كثيرة الخيرات، وهى قصبة أرمينية الوسطى، يضرب ببردها فى الشتاء المثل، وبُحَيْرَتُها يُجلَبُ منها السمك الطّرّيخ، [على وزن سكّين] ^(«٣») ، ليس فى غيرها، يُحمَلُ إلى سائرِ البلاد البعيدة، وهى من العجب، فإنها عشرة أشهر لا يوجد فيها حيوان، لا سمك ولا غيره، ثم يَظهر بها السمك مدة شهرين، فيُصاد ويكبس.","english":"Xlat: A flourishing, famous town, full of amenities, it is a fortress of Central Armenia, and its burd clothing sets an example in winter, and there is Lake Van whence one imports the pearl mullet, to which there is no equal, which is carried to the rest of the towns far away, it’s wonderful, ten months the animal is not found therein, no fish nor anything, then there appears fish for two months, and is caught and pickled."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to multiply","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pulsate, to throb, to beat (of a vein or the heart)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ache violently, to hurt severely (of a wound or tooth)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to roam, to travel","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to migrate (of a bird)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cruise (of a ship)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to incline, to tend, to shade","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"قرنوة: الغافقي: قال قوم أنها الهرنوة والقرنوة أيضاً حشيشة. […] قال أبو حنيفة: هي عشبة يضرب ورقها إلى الحمرة وهي مرة يدبغ بها. وقال أيضاً عن بعضهم: هي خضراء غبراء على ساق لها ثمرة كالسنبلة ومنابتها السهول وهي مرعى. وقال آخر: القرنوة عشبة يطول ورقها كورق الحندقوقا عفصة تستعمل في دباغة الجلود وقيل أنها هذه الحشيشة المعروفة بالأنجبار.","english":"Aloeswood. Al-Ġāfaqīy: Some say that these seeds of aloe are a herb. […] Abū Ḥanīfa: The tender leaves of this herb tend towards red and this is when they are used for tanning. And some authors said they are dingy towards the foot and have fruits like ears like spikes growing on plains and used for pasturage. Another said: It’s a plant of long leaves like honey lotus the gall of which is used for tanning hides and it has been said it is a herb known as al-anjabār."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mount (a female camel)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get the better of in beating"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be smitten by hoarfrost or rime"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give a violent hit, give a sound blow"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beat violently or repeatedly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix, mix up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stir up discord"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sew on a lining or padding"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drink of the milk called ضَرِيب (ḍarīb, “milk of several camels in the same bucket”)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get overtaken by the snow (ضَرِيب (ḍarīb, “snow, hoarfrost, ice”))"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be deep-set (of an eye)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَرَبَ (ḍaraba, “to beat”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beating, striking, hitting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"violence, power"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"haste, hurry"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the playing of musical instruments"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"minting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"multiplication"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"make, form, fashion, mold, cast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sort, species"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"report of a gun"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"similarity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"last foot of the second hemistich"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"who beats much"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"brave, bold"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active, clever"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"of a slender make and not fleshy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"slight, light"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"beaten"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"coined"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"similar, like"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضُرِبَ (ḍuriba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَرِبَ (ḍariba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/dˤa.ra.ba/","/dˤa.ri.ba/","/dˤu.ri.ba/","/dˤa.ru.ba/","/dˤar.ra.ba/","/dˤarb/","/dˤa.rab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25696","headword_ar":"ضَرْبٌ","root":"Drb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. used in the sense of a pass. part. n.; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDoruwbN","text_ar":"مَضْرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beaten, struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (K, TA:) in some of the copies of the K, it is made the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobN","text_ar":"ضَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ a species ” &c.: but this is a mistake. (TA.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirohamN DarobN","text_ar":"دِرْهَمٌ ضَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A coined dirhem"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; using the inf. n. as an epithet, as in the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N gaworN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ غَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N sakobN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ سَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA dirohamN Daroba AlA^amiyri","text_ar":"هٰذَا دِرْهَمٌ ضَرْبَ الاَمِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drb","text_ar":"ضرب"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be thus put in the accus. case as an inf. n., [the meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA dirohamN","text_ar":"هٰذَا دِرْهَمٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDoruwbN Daroba AlA^amiyri","text_ar":"مَضْرُوبٌ ضَرْبَ الاَمِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a dirhem coined with the coining of the prince,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] which is the most common way. (L, TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A light rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTarN DarobN","text_ar":"مَطَرٌ ضَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diymapN","text_ar":"دِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ a lasting, or continuous, and still, rain; ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobN","text_ar":"ضَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little more than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diymapN","text_ar":"دِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little above this:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobapN","text_ar":"ضَرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as the n. un.] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shower, of light rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A make, form, fashion, mould,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiygapN","text_ar":"صِيغَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DariybN","text_ar":"ضَرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and accord. to some copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDoruwbN","text_ar":"مَضْرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is a mistake: the pl. of the first is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuruwbN","text_ar":"ضُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A like"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a thing and of a person]; (ISd, A, K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DirobN","text_ar":"ضِرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as related on the authority of Z; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DariybN","text_ar":"ضَرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, S, A, TA;) as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dariybu Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"ضَرِيبُ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like of the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Dariybu fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ ضَرِيبُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is the like of such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobN","text_ar":"ضَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a like in stature and make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuruwbN","text_ar":"ضُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DariybN","text_ar":"ضَرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaraAy^ibu","text_ar":"ضَرَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DurabaA='u","text_ar":"ضُرَبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this latter occurring in a trad., in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba h`*aA waDurabaAw^uhu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ هٰذَا وَضُرَبَاوُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This went away, and the likes of him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daroba qawolihi","text_ar":"ضَرْبَ قَوْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the like of his saying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"referring to a saying in the Kur-án, &c.; a phrase similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHowa qawolihi","text_ar":"نَحْوَ قَوْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AZ, T voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino","text_ar":"اـِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in several places.)       -A2-  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"penetrating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vigorous and effective; light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active, in the accomplishment of an affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a want;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not flaccid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flabby, in flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And (K) a man (S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean and slender."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DurubN","text_ar":"ضُرُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to IJ, this may be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaruwbN","text_ar":"ضَرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.)       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last foot"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a verse: (K, * TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDorubN","text_ar":"اَضْرُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuruwbN","text_ar":"ضُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabN","text_ar":"ضَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Reiske, as mentioned by Freytag, explains it also as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sour milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is app. a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SarobN","text_ar":"صَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","A","S","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n25697","headword_ar":"ضِرْبٌ","root":"Drb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25698","headword_ar":"ضَرَبٌ","root":"Drb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobN","text_ar":"ضَرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former is the better known, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thick honey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white honey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick white honey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild honey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabapN","text_ar":"ضَرَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: or a portion thereof: (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabN","text_ar":"ضَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is masc. and fem.: (S:) [for] it is said to be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabapN","text_ar":"ضَرَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or a coll. gen. n., which is in most cases masc. [but is also fem.]. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n25699","headword_ar":"ضَرِبٌ","root":"Drb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miDorabN","text_ar":"مِضْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)  Herbage"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smitten and injured by the cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And (tropical:)  Herbage"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smitten by hoar-frost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rime."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN DaribapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ ضَرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land smitten by hoarfrost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rime, so that its herbage is nipped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blasted, thereby."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}